• How do you make your Javascript codes maintainable?

    - Javascript codes should be structured in a way that each class should have a single responsibility.
    If a certain function is repeatable across application, it should be a service or a plugin. Lastly, DOM manipulation
    should be separated business logic.

• What is a typical usage case for anonymous functions?

    - anonymous function typically used for callbacks especially if your doing async process

• How do you go about testing your Javascript?

    - i use automated test runners such as testem and testing frameworks such as jasmine and qunit

• How/why is usage of templates in Javascript applications important?

    - for maintainability. templates are very effective in maintaining the app specially in a large team.
    - for performance. template can be loaded asynchronously so can pull only those you need

• Explain how prototypal inheritance works.

    - it creates a new object with its prototype set to whatever you want.
